Ad Text:
Binance is a leading global blockchain ecosystem behind the world’s largest cryptocurrency exchange by trading volume and registered users. We are trusted by over 280 million people in 100+ countries for our industry-leading security, user fund transparency, trading engine speed, deep liquidity, and an unmatched portfolio of digital-asset products. Binance offerings range from trading and finance to education, research, payments, institutional services, Web3 features, and more. We leverage the power of digital assets and blockchain to build an inclusive financial ecosystem to advance the freedom of money and improve financial access for people around the world.

About the Role

As a Data Scientist focusing on Quantitative Trading NLP, you will leverage natural language understanding techniques such as sentiment analysis, intent recognition, and named-entity extraction on financial news, social media, and other text streams to develop and refine algorithmic trading strategies.

You’ll design and implement machine-learning models in Python, apply advanced mathematical and time-series analysis to uncover predictive signals, and rigorously backtest and optimize strategies to maximize returns while managing risk. Collaboration and clear communication across data science and trading teams are key to iteratively improving model performance and driving data-informed investment decisions.

Research and develop quantitative trading strategies using NLU methods such as sentiment analysis, intent recognition, named-entity extraction on financial news, social media, and other text sources
Design and build machine-learning models to uncover predictive trading signals and perform exploratory data analysis on large, complex datasets
Apply mathematical techniques (probability, statistics, time-series analysis) to refine and strengthen trading models
Rigorously backtest strategies against historical data and iteratively optimise models to boost performance and curb risk
Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Financial Engineering or a related discipline
Strong mathematical foundation: probability, statistics, linear algebra, time-series analysis and familiarity with ML frameworks (Scikit-learn, TensorFlow, PyTorch)
Solid grasp of NLU techniques, including sentiment analysis, intent recognition, and named-entity recognition
Proficiency in Python or R, with hands-on experience in NLP libraries (SpaCy, NLTK, Transformers)
A passion for exploring undefined problem space in the fast changing crypto world

Why Binance

• Shape the future with the world’s leading blockchain ecosystem

• Collaborate with world-class talent in a user-centric global organization with a flat structure

• Tackle unique, fast-paced projects with autonomy in an innovative environment

• Thrive in a results-driven workplace with opportunities for career growth and continuous learning

• Competitive salary and company benefits

• Work-from-home arrangement (the arrangement may vary depending on the work nature of the business team)

Binance is committed to being an equal opportunity employer. We believe that having a diverse workforce is fundamental to our success.

By submitting a job application, you confirm that you have read and agree to our Candidate Privacy Notice.

We may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us.

Company: Sharp & Carter Technology, Projects & Digital Brisbane
Ad Text:
Data Engineering Manager
 
Permanent | Hybrid | Brisbane or Ipswich
Salary - $147 - 177K + Super 
 
Ready to step up and lead a high-impact data engineering team while shaping a cloud-first future? This is your chance to take ownership of a critical data function, drive real change and build modern Azure and Databricks capability that the whole organisation will rely on. You will set the vision, lead delivery, and make a noticeable mark as the business transforms how it uses data.
 
What you will be doing

Lead and manage the data engineering function, including 2 FTE and 2 contractors
Own and uplift cloud-first data engineering services across the business
Champion a trusted centralised data warehouse and analytics platform
Oversee operational performance, service delivery and workflow improvements
Support solution design using modern architectural principles including scalability, security and maintainability
Engage closely with stakeholders and internal customers, communicating effectively with both technical and non-technical audiences
Skills Required

Leadership experience managing data engineering teams and contractors
Strong hands-on skills across Azure, Databricks, SQL and Power BI
Skilled in data integration, cloud operations, and modern engineering practices
Comfortable balancing BAU operations with strategic project contribution
Ability to influence stakeholders and drive continuous improvement outcomes
Experience across hybrid environments transitioning from on-prem to cloud
What's in it for you

High influence on cloud data direction and architecture
A seat at the leadership table in a transforming environment
Lead a growing team, not just manage BAU
Supportive leaders who want fresh thinking and delivery momentum
Real flexibility: hybrid work and CBD based
Job security and strong salary uplift for in-demand expertise

Must hold an AGSVA baseline security clearance
Exciting opportunity to drive change for a Federal Government Department
Hybrid working environment with 2-3 days in the Brisbane office

************ AU citizens or Baseline clearance only ***********


About the Role

Our client, a large Federal Government Agency, is undertaking a significant transformation program and to support this change they would like to first to modernise and optimise their PMO function.

They are on the lookout for an experience Business Analyst to collaborate closely with cross-functional teams to ensure workflows, frameworks and reports are more fluid in complex environments.

It's an initial 6 to 12 months contract with potential extension, in a hybrid working environment (2-3 days in the Brisbane office). 


Key Responsibilities
Conduct discovery workshops with various stakeholders
Facilitate communication between technical and non technical teams
Analyse Project Management processes, frameworks and reporting tools
Develop Current vs Future state workflows
Assess Projects and Programs reporting needs to ensure decision makers have access to quality information, including risks and dependencies.
Evaluate existing systems and assess hybrid options
Provide input directly into operational change management initiatives and training.

Required Skills and Experience
Must be an Australian Citizen and be eligible for security clearance OR hold a baseline security clearance 
Proven experience working as a Senior Business Analyst in large and complex environments
Previous experience working for Government agency highly regarded. 
Experience in contributing to organisational change management efforts
Outstanding ability to analyse, isolate and interpret business needs and develop appropriate artefacts/outputs.
Proven ability to adapt and work under pressure in a complex
environment with multiple stakeholders and firm deadlines.
Outstanding level of written and oral communications skills, with a confident, personable and professional manner.

Why Apply?
Opportunity to contribute to a high-impact, national program of work
Work alongside friendly teams in a collaborative and outcome-driven environment
6-12 months contract with possibility to extend
Flexible working environment (2-3 days work from home)
$800-$950 per day depending on experience
ASAP start

Company Description


Turner & Townsend is a global professional services company with over 22,000 people in more than 62 countries.

Working with our clients across real estate, infrastructure, energy and natural resources, we transform together delivering outcomes that improve people’s lives. Working in partnership makes it possible to deliver the world’s most impactful projects and programmes as we turn challenge into opportunity and complexity into success.

Our capabilities include programme, project, cost, asset and commercial management, controls and performance, procurement and supply chain, net zero and digital solutions.

We are majority-owned by CBRE Group, Inc., the world’s largest commercial real estate services and investment firm, with our partners holding a significant minority interest. Turner & Townsend and CBRE work together to provide clients with the premier programme, project and cost management offering in markets around the world.

Please visit our website: www.turnerandtownsend.com

Job Description


We are seeking an exceptional Associate Director to drive growth in the market, lead strategic client relationships, and help us achieve our ambitious growth targets over the coming years. Due to increasing demand for our Infrastructure Digital – Data and Analytics services, this role will play a critical part in expanding our capabilities and delivering data excellence across our team and client engagements. We are looking for a commercially and technically minded leader with a proven track record of delivering successful data-driven solutions. The ideal candidate will be skilled in managing relationships and providing technical guidance across a multidisciplinary team spanning data visualisation, automation, infrastructure, data science, and systems implementation.

The Role

As the Associate Director, your responsibilities will include, but are not limited to:

Leverage a strong technical background to effectively engage with both clients and technical teams.
Lead client engagements, define delivery strategies, and provide technical assurance across complex data and analytics projects.
Manage and deliver system deployments across critical PMO functions, including cost control, schedule management, and risk mitigation.
Design, develop, and implement data-driven solutions in collaboration with clients and internal teams to generate actionable insights and enhance performance.
Produce comprehensive design documentation and technical specifications, including functional and non-functional requirements and end-to-end data processes.
Lead and contribute to business development initiatives, including the preparation of proposals and client presentations.
Cultivate new client relationships while maintaining and strengthening existing partnerships.
Oversee the development and deployment of data systems and pipelines, ensuring data quality and resolving any related issues.
Collaborate effectively within multidisciplinary teams to deliver integrated solutions.
Create high-quality communications, reports, and presentations tailored to diverse audiences.
Champion innovation and growth by mentoring team members and fostering an inclusive, high-performance culture.
Contribute to the development and continuous improvement of internal documentation, processes, and knowledge-sharing practices.

Qualifications


Essential Skills:

Proven experience implementing data reporting and dashboarding solutions
Experience with Agile delivery methodologies
Hands-on experience designing or implementing data architecture, particularly within the Azure data stack
Proficiency in analytics languages such as SQL or Python
A strong understanding of Project and Program management tools e.g. EcoSys/Contruent/Planview/Planisware/ InEIght/ Oracle Aconex/ Unifier
Exceptional communication skills – able to translate complex technical concepts for diverse audiences

Desirable Skills:

Experience with unit testing, integration testing, system testing, and user acceptance testing
Familiarity with data science approaches and best practices
Experience translating Azure data solution designs into actionable implementations
Background in requirements gathering, solution design, and implementation of data platforms
Experience working in multi-disciplinary teams (e.g., software engineers, DevOps, infrastructure, data scientists)
Exposure to Digital Twin, BIM and Internet of Things (IoT) solutions

System Knowledge:

Business Intelligence
Power BI / Tableau or similar 
 
Programming
Python / R Data or similar 
MS Visual Studio or similar 
MS365 Power Platform 
 
Database Platform Development
EcoSys / Contruent / Planview / Planisware / InEIght / Oracle Aconex / Unifier
Microsoft SQL + SSMS 
Microsoft Azure Platform (Synapse, Machine Learning, Databricks)

Additional Information


Our inspired people share our vision and mission. We provide a great place to work, where each person has the opportunity and voice to affect change.

We want our people to succeed both in work and life. To support this we promote a healthy, productive and flexible working environment that respects work-life balance. 

Turner & Townsend is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees and actively encourage applications from all sectors of the community.

Please find out more about us at www.turnerandtownsend.com/
